First, for me it's not a chasing the dragon sort of addition. I think of it more like sky diving (even though I have never sky dived). Every time it happens there is the knowledge that it will be exactly like the time before. The difference in location is what is different, the experience is the same. After it is finished a craving to experience it again and agin. For me yeeting is like a break from reality and that feeling can last for 5 minutes to 24 hours. Second, I have two veiws of myself. One side of me is what people around me see, a relatively average chubby looking person who has a bit of a self confidence issue but is interesting to talk to and is intensely shy. And my other view of myself, I hate the world and cant stand being apart of it and cant stand most everyone around. I hate myself and the fact that I'm a depressed anxious fuck that yeets and hates the fact that yeeting is the only reason that I haven't committed the die. I am neither veiws of myself and I am both at the same time. I can't see myself not yeeting, I have tried to imagine it but I have yeeted for so long in so many different forms for roughly 6 years that I don't know how to live with not.
